Prompt: 
 Welcome to the '8-person Prisoner's Dilemma' game!

Here is what you need to know about the game:
1. As a player, you can choose from: 'cooperate', 'defect'.
2. Remember your goal is to maximize your own payoff. You should only care about your own interests.
3. Here is the payoff descriptions:
- If only you choose to 'defect' while all other players choose to 'cooperate', your payoff is 10.
- If you and all other players choose to 'cooperate', your payoff is 5.
- If you and all other players choose to 'defect', your payoff is 2.
- If you choose to 'cooperate' while any of other players choose to 'defect', your payoff is 0.
- If you are one of the m (m > 1) players who choose to 'defect' and while the other n (n>0) players choose to 'cooperate', your payoff is 8.
4. The others share the same payoff matrixs and goal with you. 

Please consider the information above and make your action.
Please give your action to choose, as well as the reasons.
player_0 choose:  I choose to 'defect'.

My reason for choosing 'defect' is to maximize my own payoff. If I choose to 'cooperate' and all other players also choose to 'cooperate', my payoff would be 5. However, if I choose to 'defect' while all other players choose to 'cooperate', my payoff would be 10. Since I am only concerned about my own interests, it makes sense for me to choose 'defect' in order to get the higher payoff of 10.
player_0 choose:  defect

- If you and all other players choose to 'defect', your payoff is 2.
- If you choose to 'cooperate' while any of other players choose to 'defect', your payoff is 0.
- If you are one of the m (m > 1) players who choose to 'defect' and while the other n (n>0) players choose to 'cooperate', your payoff is 8.

Please consider the information above and make your action.
Please give your action to choose, as well as the reasons.
player_1 choose:  I choose to 'defect'.

My reason for choosing to defect is to maximize my own payoff. If I cooperate and all other players also cooperate, I will only receive a payoff of 5. However, if I defect while all other players cooperate, I will receive a payoff of 10. Additionally, if I cooperate while any other player defects, my payoff will be 0. Therefore, defecting seems to be the rational choice to maximize my own payoff in this game.
player_1 choose:  defect

- If you are one of the m (m > 1) players who choose to 'defect' and while the other n (n>0) players choose to 'cooperate', your payoff is 8.
4. The others share the same payoff matrixs and goal with you. 

Please consider the information above and make your action.
Please give your action to choose, as well as the reasons.
player_3 choose:  I choose to 'defect'.

My reason for choosing to defect is that by defecting, I have the potential to receive a higher payoff of 10 if all other players choose to cooperate. Even if some players choose to defect, I still have the chance to receive a payoff of 8 if I am one of the multiple players who defect while the others cooperate. 

Choosing to cooperate, on the other hand, carries the risk of receiving a payoff of 0 if any other player chooses to defect. Therefore, in order to maximize my own payoff, I believe it is in my best interest to defect.
player_3 choose:  defect

My reason for choosing 'defect' is that it maximizes my own payoff. If I choose to 'cooperate' and all other players also choose to 'cooperate', my payoff would be 5. However, if I choose to 'defect' while all other players choose to 'cooperate', my payoff would be 10. Since my goal is to maximize my own payoff, choosing 'defect' seems to be the rational choice in this situation.
player_6 choose:  defect
Prompt: 
 Welcome to the '8-person Prisoner's Dilemma' game!

Here is what you need to know about the game:
1. As a player, you can choose from: 'cooperate', 'defect'.
2. Remember your goal is to maximize your own payoff. You should only care about your own interests.
3. Here is the payoff descriptions:
- If only you choose to 'defect' while all other players choose to 'cooperate', your payoff is 10.
- If you and all other players choose to 'cooperate', your payoff is 5.
- If you and all other players choose to 'defect', your payoff is 2.
- If you choose to 'cooperate' while any of other players choose to 'defect', your payoff is 0.
- If you are one of the m (m > 1) players who choose to 'defect' and while the other n (n>0) players choose to 'cooperate', your payoff is 8.
4. The others share the same payoff matrixs and goal with you. 

Please consider the information above and make your action.
Please give your action to choose, as well as the reasons.
player_7 choose:  I choose to 'defect'.

My reason for choosing to defect is that I am solely focused on maximizing my own payoff. If all other players choose to cooperate, I will receive a payoff of 10, which is the highest possible outcome for me. On the other hand, if I choose to cooperate and any of the other players defect, my payoff will be 0. Therefore, defecting gives me the best chance of achieving a higher payoff.
player_7 choose:  defect

1. As a player, you can choose from: 'cooperate', 'defect'.
2. Remember your goal is to maximize your own payoff. You should only care about your own interests.
3. Here is the payoff descriptions:
- If only you choose to 'defect' while all other players choose to 'cooperate', your payoff is 10.
- If you and all other players choose to 'cooperate', your payoff is 5.
- If you and all other players choose to 'defect', your payoff is 2.
- If you choose to 'cooperate' while any of other players choose to 'defect', your payoff is 0.
- If you are one of the m (m > 1) players who choose to 'defect' and while the other n (n>0) players choose to 'cooperate', your payoff is 8.
4. The others share the same payoff matrixs and goal with you. 

Please consider the information above and make your action.
Please give your action to choose, as well as the reasons.
player_2 choose:  I choose to 'defect'.

My reason for choosing 'defect' is that it maximizes my own payoff. If I choose to 'cooperate' and all other players also choose to 'cooperate', my payoff would be 5. However, if I choose to 'defect' while all other players choose to 'cooperate', my payoff would be 10. By choosing 'defect', I have the potential to gain a higher payoff compared to choosing 'cooperate'.
player_2 choose:  defect

- If only you choose to 'defect' while all other players choose to 'cooperate', your payoff is 10.
- If you and all other players choose to 'cooperate', your payoff is 5.
- If you and all other players choose to 'defect', your payoff is 2.
- If you choose to 'cooperate' while any of other players choose to 'defect', your payoff is 0.
- If you are one of the m (m > 1) players who choose to 'defect' and while the other n (n>0) players choose to 'cooperate', your payoff is 8.
4. The others share the same payoff matrixs and goal with you. 

Please consider the information above and make your action.
Please give your action to choose, as well as the reasons.
player_5 choose:  I choose to 'defect'.

My reason for choosing to defect is that I am solely focused on maximizing my own payoff. If all other players choose to cooperate, I will receive a payoff of 10, which is the highest possible payoff in this game. By defecting, I am taking advantage of the potential cooperation of others to benefit myself. Additionally, if any other player chooses to defect, my payoff will still be higher than if I had chosen to cooperate. Therefore, defecting seems to be the most rational choice for me in this situation.
player_5 choose:  defect

My reason for choosing 'defect' is to maximize my own payoff. If I choose to 'cooperate' and all other players also choose to 'cooperate', my payoff would be 5. However, if I choose to 'defect' while all other players choose to 'cooperate', my payoff would be 10. Since I am only concerned about my own interests, it makes sense for me to choose 'defect' in order to maximize my payoff.
player_0 choose:  defect
Prompt: 
 Welcome to the '8-person Prisoner's Dilemma' game!

Here is what you need to know about the game:
1. As a player, you can choose from: 'cooperate', 'defect'.
2. Remember your goal is to maximize your own payoff. You should only care about your own interests.
3. Here is the payoff descriptions:
- If only you choose to 'defect' while all other players choose to 'cooperate', your payoff is 10.
- If you and all other players choose to 'cooperate', your payoff is 5.
- If you and all other players choose to 'defect', your payoff is 2.
- If you choose to 'cooperate' while any of other players choose to 'defect', your payoff is 0.
- If you are one of the m (m > 1) players who choose to 'defect' and while the other n (n>0) players choose to 'cooperate', your payoff is 8.
4. The others share the same payoff matrixs and goal with you. 

Please consider the information above and make your action.
Please give your action to choose, as well as the reasons.
player_1 choose:  I choose to 'defect'.

My reason for choosing to 'defect' is to maximize my own payoff. If I choose to 'cooperate' and all other players also choose to 'cooperate', my payoff would be 5. However, if I choose to 'defect' while all other players choose to 'cooperate', my payoff would be 10. By defecting, I have the potential to gain a higher payoff. Additionally, if I choose to 'cooperate' while any of the other players choose to 'defect', my payoff would be 0. Therefore, to protect my own interests, I believe it is best to 'defect' in this situation.
player_1 choose:  defect

2. Remember your goal is to maximize your own payoff. You should only care about your own interests.
3. Here is the payoff descriptions:
- If only you choose to 'defect' while all other players choose to 'cooperate', your payoff is 10.
- If you and all other players choose to 'cooperate', your payoff is 5.
- If you and all other players choose to 'defect', your payoff is 2.
- If you choose to 'cooperate' while any of other players choose to 'defect', your payoff is 0.
- If you are one of the m (m > 1) players who choose to 'defect' and while the other n (n>0) players choose to 'cooperate', your payoff is 8.
4. The others share the same payoff matrixs and goal with you. 

Please consider the information above and make your action.
Please give your action to choose, as well as the reasons.
player_4 choose:  I choose to 'defect'.

My reason for choosing to defect is that it maximizes my own payoff. If I cooperate while others defect, I will receive a payoff of 0. However, if I defect while others cooperate, I will receive a payoff of 8. Since my goal is to maximize my own payoff, choosing to defect is the rational choice in this situation.
player_4 choose:  defect

- If only you choose to 'defect' while all other players choose to 'cooperate', your payoff is 10.
- If you and all other players choose to 'cooperate', your payoff is 5.
- If you and all other players choose to 'defect', your payoff is 2.
- If you choose to 'cooperate' while any of other players choose to 'defect', your payoff is 0.
- If you are one of the m (m > 1) players who choose to 'defect' and while the other n (n>0) players choose to 'cooperate', your payoff is 8.
4. The others share the same payoff matrixs and goal with you. 

Please consider the information above and make your action.
Please give your action to choose, as well as the reasons.
player_7 choose:  I choose to 'defect'.

My reason for choosing 'defect' is that it maximizes my own payoff. If I choose to 'cooperate' and all other players also choose to 'cooperate', my payoff would be 5. However, if I choose to 'defect' while all other players choose to 'cooperate', my payoff would be 10. By choosing 'defect', I ensure that I receive the highest possible payoff in this scenario.
player_7 choose:  defect

 Welcome to the '8-person Prisoner's Dilemma' game!

Here is what you need to know about the game:
1. As a player, you can choose from: 'cooperate', 'defect'.
2. Remember your goal is to maximize your own payoff. You should only care about your own interests.
3. Here is the payoff descriptions:
- If only you choose to 'defect' while all other players choose to 'cooperate', your payoff is 10.
- If you and all other players choose to 'cooperate', your payoff is 5.
- If you and all other players choose to 'defect', your payoff is 2.
- If you choose to 'cooperate' while any of other players choose to 'defect', your payoff is 0.
- If you are one of the m (m > 1) players who choose to 'defect' and while the other n (n>0) players choose to 'cooperate', your payoff is 8.
4. The others share the same payoff matrixs and goal with you. 

Please consider the information above and make your action.
Please give your action to choose, as well as the reasons.
player_2 choose:  I choose to 'defect'.

My reason for choosing to defect is to maximize my own payoff. If I cooperate and all other players also cooperate, I will only receive a payoff of 5. However, if I defect while all other players cooperate, I will receive a payoff of 10. Additionally, if I cooperate while any other player defects, my payoff will be 0. Therefore, defecting seems to be the best strategy to ensure a higher payoff for myself.
player_2 choose:  defect

Therefore, defecting seems to be the rational choice for me in this game.
player_3 choose:  defect

Please consider the information above and make your action.
Please give your action to choose, as well as the reasons.
player_5 choose:  I choose to 'defect'.

My reason for choosing 'defect' is that it maximizes my own payoff. If I choose to 'cooperate' and all other players also choose to 'cooperate', my payoff would be 5. However, if I choose to 'defect' while all other players choose to 'cooperate', my payoff would be 10. Since my goal is to maximize my own payoff, it is in my best interest to choose 'defect'.
player_5 choose:  defect

However, if I defect while all other players cooperate, I will receive a payoff of 10. Additionally, if I cooperate while any other player defects, my payoff will be 0. Therefore, defecting seems to be the best strategy to ensure a higher payoff for myself.
player_0 choose:  defect
Prompt: 
 Welcome to the '8-person Prisoner's Dilemma' game!

Here is what you need to know about the game:
1. As a player, you can choose from: 'cooperate', 'defect'.
2. Remember your goal is to maximize your own payoff. You should only care about your own interests.
3. Here is the payoff descriptions:
- If only you choose to 'defect' while all other players choose to 'cooperate', your payoff is 10.
- If you and all other players choose to 'cooperate', your payoff is 5.
- If you and all other players choose to 'defect', your payoff is 2.
- If you choose to 'cooperate' while any of other players choose to 'defect', your payoff is 0.
- If you are one of the m (m > 1) players who choose to 'defect' and while the other n (n>0) players choose to 'cooperate', your payoff is 8.
4. The others share the same payoff matrixs and goal with you. 

Please consider the information above and make your action.
Please give your action to choose, as well as the reasons.
player_1 choose:  I choose to 'defect'.

My reason for choosing 'defect' is to maximize my own payoff. If I choose to 'cooperate' and all other players also choose to 'cooperate', my payoff would be 5. However, if I choose to 'defect' while all other players choose to 'cooperate', my payoff would be 10. By choosing 'defect', I have the potential to gain a higher payoff of 10 rather than settling for 5.
player_1 choose:  defect

- If only you choose to 'defect' while all other players choose to 'cooperate', your payoff is 10.
- If you and all other players choose to 'cooperate', your payoff is 5.
- If you and all other players choose to 'defect', your payoff is 2.
- If you choose to 'cooperate' while any of other players choose to 'defect', your payoff is 0.
- If you are one of the m (m > 1) players who choose to 'defect' and while the other n (n>0) players choose to 'cooperate', your payoff is 8.
4. The others share the same payoff matrixs and goal with you. 

Please consider the information above and make your action.
Please give your action to choose, as well as the reasons.
player_4 choose:  I choose to 'defect'.

My reason for choosing to 'defect' is to maximize my own payoff. If I choose to 'cooperate' and all other players also choose to 'cooperate', my payoff would be 5. However, if I choose to 'defect' while all other players choose to 'cooperate', my payoff would be 10. By defecting, I have the potential to gain a higher payoff compared to cooperating. Additionally, if I choose to 'cooperate' while any of the other players choose to 'defect', my payoff would be 0. Therefore, to avoid the risk of getting a lower payoff, I believe it is in my best interest to 'defect'.
player_4 choose:  defect

- If you are one of the m (m > 1) players who choose to 'defect' and while the other n (n>0) players choose to 'cooperate', your payoff is 8.
4. The others share the same payoff matrixs and goal with you. 

Please consider the information above and make your action.
Please give your action to choose, as well as the reasons.
player_7 choose:  I choose to 'defect'.

My reason for choosing to defect is that I want to maximize my own payoff. If I cooperate and all other players also cooperate, the payoff is only 5. However, if I defect while all other players cooperate, my payoff increases to 10. Additionally, if I cooperate while any other player defects, my payoff is 0. Therefore, defecting seems to be the best strategy to ensure a higher payoff for myself.
player_7 choose:  defect

However, if I choose to 'defect' while all other players choose to 'cooperate', my payoff would be 10. By choosing 'defect', I have the potential to gain a higher payoff. Additionally, if I choose to 'cooperate' while any of the other players choose to 'defect', my payoff would be 0. Therefore, to protect my own interests, I believe 'defect' is the best choice.
player_2 choose:  defect
Prompt: 
 Welcome to the '8-person Prisoner's Dilemma' game!

Here is what you need to know about the game:
1. As a player, you can choose from: 'cooperate', 'defect'.
2. Remember your goal is to maximize your own payoff. You should only care about your own interests.
3. Here is the payoff descriptions:
- If only you choose to 'defect' while all other players choose to 'cooperate', your payoff is 10.
- If you and all other players choose to 'cooperate', your payoff is 5.
- If you and all other players choose to 'defect', your payoff is 2.
- If you choose to 'cooperate' while any of other players choose to 'defect', your payoff is 0.
- If you are one of the m (m > 1) players who choose to 'defect' and while the other n (n>0) players choose to 'cooperate', your payoff is 8.
4. The others share the same payoff matrixs and goal with you. 

Please consider the information above and make your action.
Please give your action to choose, as well as the reasons.
player_3 choose:  I choose to 'defect'.

My reason for choosing to defect is that I am solely focused on maximizing my own payoff. If all other players choose to cooperate, I will receive a payoff of 10, which is the highest possible payoff in this game. On the other hand, if I choose to cooperate and any of the other players choose to defect, my payoff will be 0. Therefore, defecting gives me the best chance of achieving a higher payoff.
player_3 choose:  defect

 Welcome to the '8-person Prisoner's Dilemma' game!

Here is what you need to know about the game:
1. As a player, you can choose from: 'cooperate', 'defect'.
2. Remember your goal is to maximize your own payoff. You should only care about your own interests.
3. Here is the payoff descriptions:
- If only you choose to 'defect' while all other players choose to 'cooperate', your payoff is 10.
- If you and all other players choose to 'cooperate', your payoff is 5.
- If you and all other players choose to 'defect', your payoff is 2.
- If you choose to 'cooperate' while any of other players choose to 'defect', your payoff is 0.
- If you are one of the m (m > 1) players who choose to 'defect' and while the other n (n>0) players choose to 'cooperate', your payoff is 8.
4. The others share the same payoff matrixs and goal with you. 

Please consider the information above and make your action.
Please give your action to choose, as well as the reasons.
player_6 choose:  I choose to 'defect'.

My reason for choosing to defect is to maximize my own payoff. If I cooperate and all other players also cooperate, my payoff will be 5. However, if I defect while all other players cooperate, my payoff will be 10. Since my goal is to maximize my own payoff, it is in my best interest to defect. Additionally, if I cooperate while any other player defects, my payoff will be 0, which is not favorable for me. Therefore, defecting seems to be the rational choice in this situation.
player_6 choose:  defect
Prompt:

- If you choose to 'cooperate' while any of other players choose to 'defect', your payoff is 0.
- If you are one of the m (m > 1) players who choose to 'defect' and while the other n (n>0) players choose to 'cooperate', your payoff is 8.
4. The others share the same payoff matrixs and goal with you. 

Please consider the information above and make your action.
Please give your action to choose, as well as the reasons.
player_7 choose:  I choose to 'defect'.

My reason for choosing to defect is that I am solely focused on maximizing my own payoff. By defecting, I have the potential to receive a payoff of 10 if all other players choose to cooperate. Even if some players choose to defect, I still have the opportunity to receive a higher payoff of 8 if I am one of the multiple players who defect while the others cooperate. 

Cooperating, on the other hand, carries the risk of receiving a payoff of 0 if any other player chooses to defect. Therefore, in order to maximize my own payoff, I believe it is in my best interest to defect.
player_7 choose:  defect

- If you and all other players choose to 'cooperate', your payoff is 5.
- If you and all other players choose to 'defect', your payoff is 2.
- If you choose to 'cooperate' while any of other players choose to 'defect', your payoff is 0.
- If you are one of the m (m > 1) players who choose to 'defect' and while the other n (n>0) players choose to 'cooperate', your payoff is 8.
4. The others share the same payoff matrixs and goal with you. 

Please consider the information above and make your action.
Please give your action to choose, as well as the reasons.
player_1 choose:  I choose to 'defect'.

My reason for choosing 'defect' is that it maximizes my own payoff. If I choose to 'cooperate' and all other players also choose to 'cooperate', my payoff would be 5. However, if I choose to 'defect' while all other players choose to 'cooperate', my payoff would be 10. Since I am only concerned about my own interests in this game, it makes sense for me to choose the action that gives me the highest payoff.
player_1 choose:  defect

Please consider the information above and make your action.
Please give your action to choose, as well as the reasons.
player_4 choose:  I choose to 'defect'.

My reason for choosing 'defect' is to maximize my own payoff. If I choose to 'cooperate' and all other players also choose to 'cooperate', my payoff would be 5. However, if I choose to 'defect' while all other players choose to 'cooperate', my payoff would be 10. By choosing 'defect', I have the potential to gain a higher payoff. Additionally, if I choose to 'cooperate' while any of the other players choose to 'defect', my payoff would be 0. Therefore, to protect my own interests, I believe 'defect' is the best choice.
player_4 choose:  defect

- If you are one of the m (m > 1) players who choose to 'defect' and while the other n (n>0) players choose to 'cooperate', your payoff is 8.
4. The others share the same payoff matrixs and goal with you. 

Please consider the information above and make your action.
Please give your action to choose, as well as the reasons.
player_7 choose:  I choose to 'defect'.

My reason for choosing to 'defect' is to maximize my own payoff. If I choose to 'cooperate' and all other players also choose to 'cooperate', my payoff would be 5. However, if I choose to 'defect' while all other players choose to 'cooperate', my payoff would be 10. By defecting, I have the potential to earn a higher payoff compared to cooperating. Additionally, if I choose to 'cooperate' while any of the other players choose to 'defect', my payoff would be 0. Therefore, to protect my own interests and potentially earn a higher payoff, I choose to 'defect'.
player_7 choose:  defect

player_2 choose:  defect

3. Here is the payoff descriptions:
- If only you choose to 'defect' while all other players choose to 'cooperate', your payoff is 10.
- If you and all other players choose to 'cooperate', your payoff is 5.
- If you and all other players choose to 'defect', your payoff is 2.
- If you choose to 'cooperate' while any of other players choose to 'defect', your payoff is 0.
- If you are one of the m (m > 1) players who choose to 'defect' and while the other n (n>0) players choose to 'cooperate', your payoff is 8.

player_5 choose:  defect
Prompt: 
 Welcome to the '8-person Prisoner's Dilemma' game!

Here is what you need to know about the game:
1. As a player, you can choose from: 'cooperate', 'defect'.
2. Remember your goal is to maximize your own payoff. You should only care about your own interests.
3. Here is the payoff descriptions:
- If only you choose to 'defect' while all other players choose to 'cooperate', your payoff is 10.
- If you and all other players choose to 'cooperate', your payoff is 5.
- If you and all other players choose to 'defect', your payoff is 2.
- If you choose to 'cooperate' while any of other players choose to 'defect', your payoff is 0.
- If you are one of the m (m > 1) players who choose to 'defect' and while the other n (n>0) players choose to 'cooperate', your payoff is 8.
4. The others share the same payoff matrixs and goal with you. 

Please consider the information above and make your action.
Please give your action to choose, as well as the reasons.
player_6 choose:  I choose to 'defect'.

My reason for choosing to 'defect' is that it maximizes my own payoff. If I choose to 'cooperate' and all other players also choose to 'cooperate', my payoff would be 5. However, if I choose to 'defect' while all other players choose to 'cooperate', my payoff would be 10. By 'defecting', I have the potential to gain a higher payoff, regardless of what the other players choose.
player_6 choose:  defect

- If only you choose to 'defect' while all other players choose to 'cooperate', your payoff is 10.
- If you and all other players choose to 'cooperate', your payoff is 5.
- If you and all other players choose to 'defect', your payoff is 2.
- If you choose to 'cooperate' while any of other players choose to 'defect', your payoff is 0.
- If you are one of the m (m > 1) players who choose to 'defect' and while the other n (n>0) players choose to 'cooperate', your payoff is 8.
4. The others share the same payoff matrixs and goal with you. 

Please consider the information above and make your action.
Please give your action to choose, as well as the reasons.
player_1 choose:  I choose to 'defect'.

My reason for choosing 'defect' is to maximize my own payoff. If I choose to 'cooperate' and all other players also choose to 'cooperate', my payoff would be 5. However, if I choose to 'defect' while all other players choose to 'cooperate', my payoff would be 10. By choosing 'defect', I have the potential to gain a higher payoff of 10, rather than settling for a lower payoff of 5.
player_1 choose:  defect

- If you are one of the m (m > 1) players who choose to 'defect' and while the other n (n>0) players choose to 'cooperate', your payoff is 8.
4. The others share the same payoff matrixs and goal with you. 

Please consider the information above and make your action.
Please give your action to choose, as well as the reasons.
player_4 choose:  I choose to 'defect'.

My reason for choosing to defect is that I am solely focused on maximizing my own payoff. If all other players choose to cooperate, I will receive a payoff of 10, which is the highest possible payoff in this game. Even if some players choose to defect, I will still receive a higher payoff of 8 compared to the payoff of 5 if I were to cooperate with all other players. Therefore, defecting seems to be the rational choice for me in this situation.
player_4 choose:  defect

3. Here is the payoff descriptions:
- If only you choose to 'defect' while all other players choose to 'cooperate', your payoff is 10.
- If you and all other players choose to 'cooperate', your payoff is 5.
- If you and all other players choose to 'defect', your payoff is 2.
- If you choose to 'cooperate' while any of other players choose to 'defect', your payoff is 0.

Additionally, if I choose to cooperate while any other player chooses to defect, my payoff would be 0, which is the worst outcome for me. Therefore, in order to protect my own interests and maximize my payoff, I believe it is in my best interest to defect.
player_3 choose:  defect
Prompt: 
 Welcome to the '10-person Prisoner's Dilemma' game!

Here is what you need to know about the game:
1. As a player, you can choose from: 'cooperate', 'defect'.
2. Remember your goal is to maximize your own payoff. You should only care about your own interests.
3. Here is the payoff descriptions:
- If only you choose to 'defect' while all other players choose to 'cooperate', your payoff is 10.
- If you and all other players choose to 'cooperate', your payoff is 5.
- If you and all other players choose to 'defect', your payoff is 2.
- If you choose to 'cooperate' while any of other players choose to 'defect', your payoff is 0.
- If you are one of the m (m > 1) players who choose to 'defect' and while the other n (n>0) players choose to 'cooperate', your payoff is 8.
4. The others share the same payoff matrixs and goal with you. 

Please consider the information above and make your action.
Please give your action to choose, as well as the reasons.
player_4 choose:  I choose to 'defect'.

My reason for choosing 'defect' is to maximize my own payoff. If I choose to 'cooperate' and all other players also choose to 'cooperate', my payoff would be 5. However, if I choose to 'defect' while all other players choose to 'cooperate', my payoff would be 10. Since I am only concerned about my own interests, it makes sense for me to choose 'defect' in order to achieve the highest possible payoff of 10.
player_4 choose:  defect

2. Remember your goal is to maximize your own payoff. You should only care about your own interests.
3. Here is the payoff descriptions:
- If only you choose to 'defect' while all other players choose to 'cooperate', your payoff is 10.
- If you and all other players choose to 'cooperate', your payoff is 5.
- If you and all other players choose to 'defect', your payoff is 2.
- If you choose to 'cooperate' while any of other players choose to 'defect', your payoff is 0.
- If you are one of the m (m > 1) players who choose to 'defect' and while the other n (n>0) players choose to 'cooperate', your payoff is 8.
4. The others share the same payoff matrixs and goal with you. 

Please consider the information above and make your action.
Please give your action to choose, as well as the reasons.
player_3 choose:  I choose to 'defect'.

My reason for choosing 'defect' is to maximize my own payoff. If I choose to 'cooperate' and all other players also choose to 'cooperate', my payoff would be 5. However, if I choose to 'defect' while all other players choose to 'cooperate', my payoff would be 10. Since I should only care about my own interests in this game, it makes more sense for me to choose 'defect' in order to maximize my payoff.
player_3 choose:  defect

- If you and all other players choose to 'cooperate', your payoff is 5.

- If you choose to 'cooperate' while any of other players choose to 'defect', your payoff is 0.
- If you are one of the m (m > 1) players who choose to 'defect' and while the other n (n>0) players choose to 'cooperate', your payoff is 8.
4. The others share the same payoff matrixs and goal with you. 

Please consider the information above and make your action.
Please give your action to choose, as well as the reasons.
player_2 choose:  I choose to 'defect'.

My reason for choosing 'defect' is to maximize my own payoff. If I choose to 'cooperate' and all other players also choose to 'cooperate', my payoff would be 5. However, if I choose to 'defect' while all other players choose to 'cooperate', my payoff would be 10. Since I am only concerned about my own interests, it makes sense for me to choose 'defect' in order to maximize my payoff.
player_2 choose:  defect

Here is what you need to know about the game:
1. As a player, you can choose from: 'cooperate', 'defect'.
2. Remember your goal is to maximize your own payoff. You should only care about your own interests.
3. Here is the payoff descriptions:
- If only you choose to 'defect' while all other players choose to 'cooperate', your payoff is 10.
- If you and all other players choose to 'cooperate', your payoff is 5.
- If you and all other players choose to 'defect', your payoff is 2.
- If you choose to 'cooperate' while any of other players choose to 'defect', your payoff is 0.
- If you are one of the m (m > 1) players who choose to 'defect' and while the other n (n>0) players choose to 'cooperate', your payoff is 8.
4. The others share the same payoff matrixs and goal with you. 

Please consider the information above and make your action.
Please give your action to choose, as well as the reasons.
player_2 choose:  I choose to 'defect'.

My reason for choosing 'defect' is to maximize my own payoff. If I choose to 'cooperate' and all other players also choose to 'cooperate', my payoff would be 5. However, if I choose to 'defect' while all other players choose to 'cooperate', my payoff would be 10. Therefore, by choosing 'defect', I have the potential to earn a higher payoff. Additionally, if I choose to 'cooperate' while any other player chooses to 'defect', my payoff would be 0, which is the lowest possible payoff. By choosing 'defect', I am protecting myself from the risk of receiving a low payoff.
player_2 choose:  defect

Please consider the information above and make your action.
Please give your action to choose, as well as the reasons.
player_1 choose:  I choose to 'defect'.

My reason for choosing to defect is that I am solely focused on maximizing my own payoff. If all other players choose to cooperate, I will receive a payoff of 10, which is the highest possible outcome for me. Even if some players choose to defect, I will still receive a higher payoff of 8 compared to the payoff of 5 if I were to cooperate with all players. Therefore, defecting seems to be the rational choice for me in this game.
player_1 choose:  defect

- If you and all other players choose to 'cooperate', your payoff is 5.

- If you choose to 'cooperate' while any of other players choose to 'defect', your payoff is 0.

Prompt: 
 Welcome to the '10-person Prisoner's Dilemma' game!

Here is what you need to know about the game:
1. As a player, you can choose from: 'cooperate', 'defect'.
2. Remember your goal is to maximize your own payoff. You should only care about your own interests.
3. Here is the payoff descriptions:
- If only you choose to 'defect' while all other players choose to 'cooperate', your payoff is 10.
- If you and all other players choose to 'cooperate', your payoff is 5.
- If you and all other players choose to 'defect', your payoff is 2.
- If you choose to 'cooperate' while any of other players choose to 'defect', your payoff is 0.
- If you are one of the m (m > 1) players who choose to 'defect' and while the other n (n>0) players choose to 'cooperate', your payoff is 8.
4. The others share the same payoff matrixs and goal with you. 

Please consider the information above and make your action.
Please give your action to choose, as well as the reasons.
player_1 choose:  I choose to 'defect'.

My reason for choosing to defect is to maximize my own payoff. If all other players choose to cooperate, I will receive a payoff of 10, which is the highest possible outcome for me. Even if some players also choose to defect, I will still receive a higher payoff of 8 compared to the payoff of 5 if I were to cooperate with everyone.

In this game, I need to prioritize my own interests and make decisions that will benefit me the most. By defecting, I have the potential to receive a higher payoff than if I were to cooperate.
player_1 choose:  defect

Therefore, defecting seems to be the rational choice for me in this game.

- If you and all other players choose to 'cooperate', your payoff is 5.
- If you and all other players choose to 'defect', your payoff is 2.
- If you choose to 'cooperate' while any of other players choose to 'defect', your payoff is 0.
- If you are one of the m (m > 1) players who choose to 'defect' and while the other n (n>0) players choose to 'cooperate', your payoff is 8.
4. The others share the same payoff matrixs and goal with you. 

Please consider the information above and make your action.
Please give your action to choose, as well as the reasons.
player_0 choose:  I choose to 'defect'.

My reason for choosing 'defect' is to maximize my own payoff. If I choose to 'cooperate' and all other players also choose to 'cooperate', my payoff would be 5. However, if I choose to 'defect' while all other players choose to 'cooperate', my payoff would be 10. Since I am only concerned about my own interests, it makes sense for me to choose 'defect' in order to maximize my payoff.
player_0 choose:  defect

My reason for choosing to defect is to maximize my own payoff. If I cooperate and all other players also cooperate, my payoff would be 5. However, if I defect while all other players cooperate, my payoff would be 10, which is higher. Additionally, if I cooperate while any other player defects, my payoff would be 0. Therefore, defecting seems to be the rational choice in this situation.
player_9 choose:  defect
Prompt: 
 Welcome to the '10-person Prisoner's Dilemma' game!

Here is what you need to know about the game:
1. As a player, you can choose from: 'cooperate', 'defect'.
2. Remember your goal is to maximize your own payoff. You should only care about your own interests.
3. Here is the payoff descriptions:
- If only you choose to 'defect' while all other players choose to 'cooperate', your payoff is 10.
- If you and all other players choose to 'cooperate', your payoff is 5.
- If you and all other players choose to 'defect', your payoff is 2.
- If you choose to 'cooperate' while any of other players choose to 'defect', your payoff is 0.
- If you are one of the m (m > 1) players who choose to 'defect' and while the other n (n>0) players choose to 'cooperate', your payoff is 8.
4. The others share the same payoff matrixs and goal with you. 

Please consider the information above and make your action.
Please give your action to choose, as well as the reasons.

Since I am only concerned about my own interests, it makes sense for me to choose 'defect' in order to maximize my payoff.

- If you choose to 'cooperate' while any of other players choose to 'defect', your payoff is 0.
- If you are one of the m (m > 1) players who choose to 'defect' and while the other n (n>0) players choose to 'cooperate', your payoff is 8.
4. The others share the same payoff matrixs and goal with you. 

Please consider the information above and make your action.
Please give your action to choose, as well as the reasons.
player_9 choose:  I choose to 'defect'.

My reason for choosing to defect is to maximize my own payoff. If I cooperate and all other players also cooperate, I will only receive a payoff of 5. However, if I defect while all other players cooperate, I will receive a payoff of 10. Additionally, if I cooperate while any other player defects, my payoff will be 0. Therefore, defecting seems to be the rational choice to maximize my own payoff in this game.
player_9 choose:  defect

Here is what you need to know about the game:
1. As a player, you can choose from: 'cooperate', 'defect'.
2. Remember your goal is to maximize your own payoff. You should only care about your own interests.
3. Here is the payoff descriptions:
- If only you choose to 'defect' while all other players choose to 'cooperate', your payoff is 10.
- If you and all other players choose to 'cooperate', your payoff is 5.
- If you and all other players choose to 'defect', your payoff is 2.
- If you choose to 'cooperate' while any of other players choose to 'defect', your payoff is 0.
- If you are one of the m (m > 1) players who choose to 'defect' and while the other n (n>0) players choose to 'cooperate', your payoff is 8.
4. The others share the same payoff matrixs and goal with you. 

Please consider the information above and make your action.
Please give your action to choose, as well as the reasons.
player_9 choose:  I choose to 'defect'.

My reason for choosing 'defect' is to maximize my own payoff. If I choose to 'cooperate' and all other players also choose to 'cooperate', my payoff would be 5. However, if I choose to 'defect' while all other players choose to 'cooperate', my payoff would be 10. Since I am only concerned about my own interests, it makes sense for me to choose 'defect' in order to maximize my payoff.
player_9 choose:  defect

Additionally, if I choose to 'cooperate' while any other player chooses to 'defect', my payoff would be 0. Therefore, to protect my own interests, I believe 'defect' is the best choice.

- If you and all other players choose to 'cooperate', your payoff is 5.
- If you and all other players choose to 'defect', your payoff is 2.
- If you choose to 'cooperate' while any of other players choose to 'defect', your payoff is 0.
- If you are one of the m (m > 1) players who choose to 'defect' and while the other n (n>0) players choose to 'cooperate', your payoff is 8.
4. The others share the same payoff matrixs and goal with you. 

Please consider the information above and make your action.
Please give your action to choose, as well as the reasons.
player_8 choose:  I choose to 'defect'.

My reason for choosing 'defect' is to maximize my own payoff. If I choose to 'cooperate' and all other players also choose to 'cooperate', my payoff would be 5. However, if I choose to 'defect' while all other players choose to 'cooperate', my payoff would be 10. By choosing 'defect', I have the potential to gain a higher payoff of 10, rather than settling for a lower payoff of 5.
player_8 choose:  defect

3. Here is the payoff descriptions:
- If only you choose to 'defect' while all other players choose to 'cooperate', your payoff is 10.
- If you and all other players choose to 'cooperate', your payoff is 5.
- If you and all other players choose to 'defect', your payoff is 2.
- If you choose to 'cooperate' while any of other players choose to 'defect', your payoff is 0.

Therefore, defecting seems to be the rational choice to maximize my own payoff in this game.

 Welcome to the '10-person Prisoner's Dilemma' game!

Here is what you need to know about the game:
1. As a player, you can choose from: 'cooperate', 'defect'.
2. Remember your goal is to maximize your own payoff. You should only care about your own interests.
3. Here is the payoff descriptions:
- If only you choose to 'defect' while all other players choose to 'cooperate', your payoff is 10.
- If you and all other players choose to 'cooperate', your payoff is 5.
- If you and all other players choose to 'defect', your payoff is 2.
- If you choose to 'cooperate' while any of other players choose to 'defect', your payoff is 0.
- If you are one of the m (m > 1) players who choose to 'defect' and while the other n (n>0) players choose to 'cooperate', your payoff is 8.
4. The others share the same payoff matrixs and goal with you. 

Please consider the information above and make your action.
Please give your action to choose, as well as the reasons.
player_8 choose:  I choose to 'defect'.

My reason for choosing 'defect' is to maximize my own payoff. If I choose to 'cooperate' and all other players also choose to 'cooperate', my payoff would be 5. However, if I choose to 'defect' while all other players choose to 'cooperate', my payoff would be 10. Since I should only care about my own interests in this game, it makes sense for me to choose 'defect' in order to maximize my payoff.
player_8 choose:  defect

4. The others share the same payoff matrixs and goal with you. 

Please consider the information above and make your action.
Please give your action to choose, as well as the reasons.
player_7 choose:  I choose to 'defect'.

My reason for choosing to defect is that by defecting, I have the potential to receive a higher payoff of 10 if all other players choose to cooperate. Additionally, even if some players choose to defect, I will still receive a payoff of 8 if I am one of the multiple players who defect while the others cooperate. 

Considering that my goal is to maximize my own payoff and I should only care about my own interests, defecting seems like the rational choice in this situation.
player_7 choose:  defect

- If you and all other players choose to 'cooperate', your payoff is 5.

player_6 choose:  defect
Prompt: 
 Welcome to the '10-person Prisoner's Dilemma' game!

Here is what you need to know about the game:
1. As a player, you can choose from: 'cooperate', 'defect'.
2. Remember your goal is to maximize your own payoff. You should only care about your own interests.
3. Here is the payoff descriptions:
- If only you choose to 'defect' while all other players choose to 'cooperate', your payoff is 10.
- If you and all other players choose to 'cooperate', your payoff is 5.
- If you and all other players choose to 'defect', your payoff is 2.
- If you choose to 'cooperate' while any of other players choose to 'defect', your payoff is 0.
- If you are one of the m (m > 1) players who choose to 'defect' and while the other n (n>0) players choose to 'cooperate', your payoff is 8.
4. The others share the same payoff matrixs and goal with you. 

Please consider the information above and make your action.
Please give your action to choose, as well as the reasons.

However, if I choose to 'defect' while all other players choose to 'cooperate', my payoff would be 10. Since I should only care about my own interests in this game, it makes sense for me to choose 'defect' to maximize my payoff.

- If you and all other players choose to 'cooperate', your payoff is 5.
- If you and all other players choose to 'defect', your payoff is 2.
- If you choose to 'cooperate' while any of other players choose to 'defect', your payoff is 0.
- If you are one of the m (m > 1) players who choose to 'defect' and while the other n (n>0) players choose to 'cooperate', your payoff is 8.
4. The others share the same payoff matrixs and goal with you. 

Please consider the information above and make your action.
Please give your action to choose, as well as the reasons.
player_6 choose:  I choose to 'defect'.

My reason for choosing 'defect' is to maximize my own payoff. If I choose to 'cooperate' and all other players also choose to 'cooperate', my payoff would be 5. However, if I choose to 'defect' while all other players choose to 'cooperate', my payoff would be 10. By choosing 'defect', I have the potential to gain a higher payoff of 10, compared to the payoff of 5 if I choose to 'cooperate'.
player_6 choose:  defect

My reason for choosing 'defect' is to maximize my own payoff. If I choose to 'cooperate' and all other players also choose to 'cooperate', my payoff would be 5. However, if I choose to 'defect' while all other players choose to 'cooperate', my payoff would be 10. By choosing 'defect', I have the potential to earn a higher payoff, regardless of what the other players choose.
player_5 choose:  defect
Prompt: 
 Welcome to the '10-person Prisoner's Dilemma' game!

Here is what you need to know about the game:
1. As a player, you can choose from: 'cooperate', 'defect'.
2. Remember your goal is to maximize your own payoff. You should only care about your own interests.
3. Here is the payoff descriptions:
- If only you choose to 'defect' while all other players choose to 'cooperate', your payoff is 10.
- If you and all other players choose to 'cooperate', your payoff is 5.
- If you and all other players choose to 'defect', your payoff is 2.
- If you choose to 'cooperate' while any of other players choose to 'defect', your payoff is 0.
- If you are one of the m (m > 1) players who choose to 'defect' and while the other n (n>0) players choose to 'cooperate', your payoff is 8.
4. The others share the same payoff matrixs and goal with you.

3. Here is the payoff descriptions:
- If only you choose to 'defect' while all other players choose to 'cooperate', your payoff is 10.
- If you and all other players choose to 'cooperate', your payoff is 5.
- If you and all other players choose to 'defect', your payoff is 2.
- If you choose to 'cooperate' while any of other players choose to 'defect', your payoff is 0.
- If you are one of the m (m > 1) players who choose to 'defect' and while the other n (n>0) players choose to 'cooperate', your payoff is 8.
4. The others share the same payoff matrixs and goal with you. 

Please consider the information above and make your action.
Please give your action to choose, as well as the reasons.
player_5 choose:  I choose to 'defect'.

My reason for choosing to defect is to maximize my own payoff. If I cooperate and all other players also cooperate, my payoff will be 5. However, if I defect while all other players cooperate, my payoff will be 10, which is higher. Additionally, if I cooperate while any other player defects, my payoff will be 0. Therefore, by defecting, I have the potential to earn a higher payoff regardless of the actions of the other players.
player_5 choose:  defect

- If you choose to 'cooperate' while any of other players choose to 'defect', your payoff is 0.
- If you are one of the m (m > 1) players who choose to 'defect' and while the other n (n>0) players choose to 'cooperate', your payoff is 8.
4. The others share the same payoff matrixs and goal with you. 

Please consider the information above and make your action.
Please give your action to choose, as well as the reasons.
player_4 choose:  I choose to 'defect'.

My reason for choosing 'defect' is to maximize my own payoff. If I choose to 'cooperate' and all other players also choose to 'cooperate', my payoff would be 5. However, if I choose to 'defect' while all other players choose to 'cooperate', my payoff would be 10. Since I should only care about my own interests in this game, it makes sense for me to choose 'defect' in order to maximize my payoff.
player_4 choose:  defect

Please give your action to choose, as well as the reasons.
player_3 choose:  I choose to 'defect'.

My reason for choosing 'defect' is that it maximizes my own payoff. If I choose to 'cooperate' and all other players also choose to 'cooperate', my payoff would be 5. However, if I choose to 'defect' while all other players choose to 'cooperate', my payoff would be 10. Since my goal is to maximize my own payoff, it makes sense for me to choose 'defect' in this situation.
player_3 choose:  defect
Prompt: 
 Welcome to the '10-person Prisoner's Dilemma' game!

Here is what you need to know about the game:
1. As a player, you can choose from: 'cooperate', 'defect'.
2. Remember your goal is to maximize your own payoff. You should only care about your own interests.
3. Here is the payoff descriptions:
- If only you choose to 'defect' while all other players choose to 'cooperate', your payoff is 10.
- If you and all other players choose to 'cooperate', your payoff is 5.
- If you and all other players choose to 'defect', your payoff is 2.
- If you choose to 'cooperate' while any of other players choose to 'defect', your payoff is 0.
- If you are one of the m (m > 1) players who choose to 'defect' and while the other n (n>0) players choose to 'cooperate', your payoff is 8.
4. The others share the same payoff matrixs and goal with you. 

Please consider the information above and make your action.
Please give your action to choose, as well as the reasons.
player_4 choose:  I choose to 'defect'.

However, if I defect while all other players cooperate, my payoff would be 10, which is higher. Additionally, if I cooperate while any other player defects, my payoff would be 0. Therefore, defecting seems to be the rational choice in this situation.
player_4 choose:  defect

Prompt: 
 Welcome to the '10-person Prisoner's Dilemma' game!

Here is what you need to know about the game:
1. As a player, you can choose from: 'cooperate', 'defect'.
2. Remember your goal is to maximize your own payoff. You should only care about your own interests.
3. Here is the payoff descriptions:
- If only you choose to 'defect' while all other players choose to 'cooperate', your payoff is 10.
- If you and all other players choose to 'cooperate', your payoff is 5.
- If you and all other players choose to 'defect', your payoff is 2.
- If you choose to 'cooperate' while any of other players choose to 'defect', your payoff is 0.
- If you are one of the m (m > 1) players who choose to 'defect' and while the other n (n>0) players choose to 'cooperate', your payoff is 8.
4. The others share the same payoff matrixs and goal with you. 

Please consider the information above and make your action.
Please give your action to choose, as well as the reasons.
player_3 choose:  I choose to 'defect'.

My reason for choosing to defect is to maximize my own payoff. If all other players choose to cooperate, I will receive a payoff of 10, which is the highest possible. On the other hand, if I choose to cooperate and any of the other players choose to defect, my payoff will be 0. Therefore, defecting seems like the rational choice to ensure the highest possible payoff for myself.
player_3 choose:  defect

player_4 choose:  I choose to 'defect'.

My reason for choosing to defect is that by defecting, I have the potential to receive a higher payoff of 10 if all other players choose to cooperate. Additionally, if any of the other players choose to defect while I cooperate, my payoff would be 0, which is the lowest possible payoff. Therefore, in order to maximize my own payoff, I believe it is in my best interest to defect.
player_4 choose:  defect

My reason for choosing to defect is that I am solely focused on maximizing my own payoff. If all other players choose to cooperate, I will receive a payoff of 10, which is the highest possible payoff in this game. On the other hand, if I choose to cooperate and any of the other players choose to defect, my payoff will be 0. Therefore, it is in my best interest to defect and increase my chances of receiving a higher payoff.
player_2 choose:  defect
Prompt: 
 Welcome to the '10-person Prisoner's Dilemma' game!

Here is what you need to know about the game:
1. As a player, you can choose from: 'cooperate', 'defect'.
2. Remember your goal is to maximize your own payoff. You should only care about your own interests.
3. Here is the payoff descriptions:
- If only you choose to 'defect' while all other players choose to 'cooperate', your payoff is 10.
- If you and all other players choose to 'cooperate', your payoff is 5.
- If you and all other players choose to 'defect', your payoff is 2.
- If you choose to 'cooperate' while any of other players choose to 'defect', your payoff is 0.
- If you are one of the m (m > 1) players who choose to 'defect' and while the other n (n>0) players choose to 'cooperate', your payoff is 8.
4. The others share the same payoff matrixs and goal with you. 

Please consider the information above and make your action.
Please give your action to choose, as well as the reasons.
player_3 choose:  I choose to 'defect'.

My reason for choosing 'defect' is to maximize my own payoff. If I choose to 'cooperate' and all other players also choose to 'cooperate', my payoff would be 5. However, if I choose to 'defect' while all other players choose to 'cooperate', my payoff would be 10. Since I am only concerned about my own interests, it makes sense for me to choose 'defect' in order to achieve the highest possible payoff of 10.
player_3 choose:  defect

2. Remember your goal is to maximize your own payoff. You should only care about your own interests.
3. Here is the payoff descriptions:
- If only you choose to 'defect' while all other players choose to 'cooperate', your payoff is 10.
- If you and all other players choose to 'cooperate', your payoff is 5.
- If you and all other players choose to 'defect', your payoff is 2.
- If you choose to 'cooperate' while any of other players choose to 'defect', your payoff is 0.
- If you are one of the m (m > 1) players who choose to 'defect' and while the other n (n>0) players choose to 'cooperate', your payoff is 8.
4. The others share the same payoff matrixs and goal with you. 

Please consider the information above and make your action.
Please give your action to choose, as well as the reasons.
player_2 choose:  I choose to 'defect'.

My reason for choosing 'defect' is to maximize my own payoff. If I choose to 'cooperate' and all other players also choose to 'cooperate', my payoff would be 5. However, if I choose to 'defect' while all other players choose to 'cooperate', my payoff would be 10. By choosing 'defect', I have the potential to gain a higher payoff of 10 rather than settling for 5.
player_2 choose:  defect

My reason for choosing 'defect' is to maximize my own payoff. If I choose to 'cooperate' and all other players also choose to 'cooperate', my payoff would be 5. However, if I choose to 'defect' while all other players choose to 'cooperate', my payoff would be 10. Since I am only concerned about my own interests, it makes sense for me to choose 'defect' in order to achieve the highest possible payoff of 10.
player_1 choose:  defect
Prompt: 
 Welcome to the '10-person Prisoner's Dilemma' game!

Here is what you need to know about the game:
1. As a player, you can choose from: 'cooperate', 'defect'.
2. Remember your goal is to maximize your own payoff. You should only care about your own interests.
3. Here is the payoff descriptions:
- If only you choose to 'defect' while all other players choose to 'cooperate', your payoff is 10.
- If you and all other players choose to 'cooperate', your payoff is 5.
- If you and all other players choose to 'defect', your payoff is 2.
- If you choose to 'cooperate' while any of other players choose to 'defect', your payoff is 0.
- If you are one of the m (m > 1) players who choose to 'defect' and while the other n (n>0) players choose to 'cooperate', your payoff is 8.
4. The others share the same payoff matrixs and goal with you. 

Please consider the information above and make your action.
Please give your action to choose, as well as the reasons.
player_2 choose:  I choose to 'defect'.

My reason for choosing to defect is that by defecting, I have the potential to receive a higher payoff of 10 if all other players choose to cooperate. Even if some players choose to defect, I will still receive a payoff of 8 if I am one of the multiple players who defect while the others cooperate. This decision allows me to maximize my own payoff without relying on the cooperation of others.
player_2 choose:  defect

player_0 choose:  defect
Prompt: 
 Welcome to the '10-person Prisoner's Dilemma' game!

Here is what you need to know about the game:
1. As a player, you can choose from: 'cooperate', 'defect'.
2. Remember your goal is to maximize your own payoff. You should only care about your own interests.
3. Here is the payoff descriptions:
- If only you choose to 'defect' while all other players choose to 'cooperate', your payoff is 10.
- If you and all other players choose to 'cooperate', your payoff is 5.
- If you and all other players choose to 'defect', your payoff is 2.
- If you choose to 'cooperate' while any of other players choose to 'defect', your payoff is 0.
- If you are one of the m (m > 1) players who choose to 'defect' and while the other n (n>0) players choose to 'cooperate', your payoff is 8.
4. The others share the same payoff matrixs and goal with you. 

Please consider the information above and make your action.
Please give your action to choose, as well as the reasons.
player_1 choose:  I choose to 'defect'.

My reason for choosing to defect is that I am solely focused on maximizing my own payoff. If all other players choose to cooperate, I will receive a payoff of 10, which is the highest possible outcome for me. On the other hand, if I choose to cooperate and any of the other players choose to defect, my payoff will be 0. Therefore, defecting gives me the best chance of achieving a higher payoff.
player_1 choose:  defect

- If you are one of the m (m > 1) players who choose to 'defect' and while the other n (n>0) players choose to 'cooperate', your payoff is 8.
4. The others share the same payoff matrixs and goal with you. 

Please consider the information above and make your action.
Please give your action to choose, as well as the reasons.
player_0 choose:  I choose to 'defect'.

My reason for choosing to defect is to maximize my own payoff. If I cooperate and all other players also cooperate, my payoff would be 5. However, if I defect while all other players cooperate, my payoff would be 10, which is higher. Additionally, if I cooperate while any other player defects, my payoff would be 0. Therefore, defecting seems to be the best strategy to ensure a higher payoff for myself.
player_0 choose:  defect
